OL,3,CStarmer faces backbench anger after
OL,4,C'day one' workers' right U-turn
OL,6,FMinisters have axed the proposal to
OL,7,Fcut the "qualifying period" for
OL,8,Fworkers to make an unfair dismissal
OL,9,Fclaim from 24 months to the first day
OL,10,Fin a new job, in a bid to get the
OL,11,Flegislation through Parliament.
OL,13,FThe Bill had been caught in a stand-
OL,14,Foff between peers and MPs over the
OL,15,Foriginal plan to give workers the
OL,16,Fprotection on day one, as well as
OL,17,Fmeasures to ban "exploitative" zero-
OL,18,Fhours contracts.
